  <div class="row">
    <h2>/interactions*</h2>
    <p>Log the interactions your bots have in order to get access to analytics and suggested changes.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="row">
    <h3>POST /interactions/log.json</h3>
    <p><b>Parameters Required:</b> [account_name, bot_name, platform, user_id, bot_rule, time, user_input, bot_response]</p>
    <p><b>Description:</b> Log an interaction with a user engaging with the bot</p>
    <b>Example:</b><br/>
    <pre><code class="language-bash">
      curl --user gooble:gobble -H "Content-Type: application/json" -X POST -d '{"account_name":"abc","bot_name":"xyz","platform":"twitter","user_id":"abc123","bot_rule":"bot do *","time":"2016-07-06 02:12:09 -0400","user_input":"Hi bot!","bot_response":"[{\"text\" => \"Hey human, how goes it?\"}]"}' http://ec2-54-208-153-78.compute-1.amazonaws.com/interactions/log.json
    </code></pre>
  </div>
  <div class="row">
    <h2>/user_blacklists*</h2>
    <p>Add or remove people from analysis</p>
  </div>
  <div class="row">
    <h3>POST /user_blacklists/add_user.json</h3>
    <p><b>Parameters Required:</b> [account_name, bot_name, platform, user_id]</p>
    <p><b>Description:</b> Remove a person from the interactions that should be logged (e.g. bot testers, staff trying out the bot)</p>
    <b>Example:</b><br/>
    <pre><code class="language-bash">
      curl --user gooble:gobble -H "Content-Type: application/json" -X POST -d '{"account_name":"abc","bot_name":"xyz", "platform": "facebook", "user_id":"abc123"}' http://ec2-54-208-153-78.compute-1.amazonaws.com/user_blacklists/add_user.json
    </code></pre>
  </div>
  <div class="row">
    <h3>POST /user_blacklists/drop_user.json</h3>
    <p><b>Parameters Required:</b> [account_name, bot_name, platform, user_id]</p>
